    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Buildings or rooms built or used for the containment of smoke, usually such buildings or rooms where meat or fish is dried or cured by means of dense smoke. Also, rooms or structures in a tannery that are heated by smoldering bark and used to unhair hides.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
